20/11/2008
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The new president of The Hague war crimes tribunal, Jamaican judge Patrick Robinson, has decided that another official must replace him as a judge in the trial of former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, the tribunal said in a statement Wednesday (November 19th). Robinson, who took over as president on Monday, will surrender his role in Karadzic's case to German judge Christoph Flieger. Karadzic, a former Bosnian Serb leader, allegedly committed genocide, war crimes and violations of the rules and traditions of war during the armed conflict in Bosnia from 1992 to 1995. (Tanjug, B92 - 19/11/08)
